Package Users

package Users
The `Users` package contains classes and interfaces that define various user roles and their attributes within the system. This package is responsible for managing and representing different types of users, including students, staff, and administrators. It provides a structured way to store user information, roles, and interactions with the system. The classes and interfaces here facilitate user authentication, profile management, and access control. Users of the system are categorized into different roles, each with specific privileges and responsibilities. These roles include `Student`, `Staff`, and `Administrator`, each having their own set of attributes and behaviors.
  • Class
    Description
    AdminUser
    The `AdminUser` class represents an administrative user in the system.
    Attendee
    The `Attendee` class represents an attendee in the system, associated with a student.
    Authentication
    The `Authentication` class represents user authentication information, including username and password.
    BusyDate
    The `BusyDate` class represents a list of dates that are marked as busy.
    Committee
    The `Committee` class represents a committee member in a camp, associated with a specific camp and student.
    Faculty
    The `Faculty` class represents the various faculties at a university.

    All the faculties in NTU, each student only associated to one Faculty.
